plines, from psychology to business to religious studies to art. Included here are perspectives by scholars in the continental, comparativist, and process traditions who dive into integral theory's postmetaphysical claims in order to mine, extend, and critique its philosophical merits. On the verge of its own emergence, integral philosophy promotes modes of creative critical thought oriented toward the multidimensional flourishing of planetary well-being, and Dancing with Sophia will be of interest to scholars in philosophy; religious studies; transpersonal, developmental, and humanist psychology; and more.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aMetatheory. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPsychology : Integral Theory. 4aPsychology : Psychology. 4aPsychology : Transpersonal Psychology. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Movements / Transpersonal.2bisacsh1 aAlderman, Bruce, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCabot, Zayin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDesilet, Gregory, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEsbjörn-Hargens, Sean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEsbjörn-Hargens, Sean, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFreeman, Cameron Stewart Rees, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHedlund, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMatuštík, Martin Beck, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMickey, Sam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMurray, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchroeder, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchwartz, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https: